            "sub_category": "Sports, Exercise, and Nutrition",
            "summary": "**Summary: Domain-Specific Expertise Enhancement in Sports, Exercise, and Nutrition**\n\nThe theme of Domain-Specific Expertise Enhancement in Sports, Exercise, and Nutrition reflects the targeted application of AI to augment professional knowledge and decision-making in highly specialized, evidence-based contexts. Rather than replacing human expertise, AI serves as a precise, research-oriented tool that delivers accurate, science-backed recommendations for narrow, well-defined queries. In rehabilitation settings, practitioners leverage AI to identify optimal exercise protocols\u2014such as shoulder-specific movements aligned with physical therapy goals\u2014while nutritionists use it to tailor dietary strategies for conditions like hormonal imbalances or injury recovery. Similarly, athletes and sports professionals employ AI as a supplementary resource to refine performance strategies, accessing evidence-based insights on sport science and nutritional planning that complement their existing knowledge. Critically, AI\u2019s effectiveness is maximized when used in isolation for focused, research-driven tasks; its utility diminishes when embedded in complex, holistic client plans where contextual nuance is essential. Thus, this theme underscores a synergistic model: AI enhances\u2014rather than supersedes\u2014human expertise by providing rapid, reliable, and domain-specific guidance in exercise, nutrition, and sports science.",
